1 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
2 Sec. 1. 20 V.S.A. § 4652 is amended to read:
3 § 4652. AUTHORIZATION TO ENTER INTO AGREEMENTS
4 PURSUANT TO 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) AND 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i)
5 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, only the Governor, in
6 consultation with the Vermont Attorney General upon approval from the
7 General Assembly as set forth in subsection (b) of this section, is authorized to
8 enter into, modify, or extend an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or
9 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i).
10 (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, a State, county, or
11 municipal law enforcement agency is authorized to enter into an agreement
12 pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) when necessary to
13 address threats to the public safety or welfare of Vermont residents arising out
14 of a declaration of a State or national emergency.
15 (1) The Governor shall not enter into an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C.
16 § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) without prior approval from the General
17 Assembly.
18 (2) Not fewer than 60 days before the General Assembly may vote on a
19 proposed agreement pursuant to subdivision (1) of this subsection, the
20 Governor shall:
21 (A) provide the General Assembly with:
