1 (i) the full text of the proposed agreement; and
2 (ii) an analysis of the potential fiscal, social, and legal impacts of
3 the agreement; and
4 (B) hold one or more public hearings in order to inform and gather
5 input from Vermonters, including immigrant advocacy organizations, on the
6 proposed agreement.
7 (3) No agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i)
8 shall be entered into if the General Assembly is not in session.
9 (4) No State, county, or municipal law enforcement agency or officer
10 shall engage in any duty or action pursuant to an 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or
11 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) agreement unless the General Assembly approves of such
12 agreement as set forth in subdivision (1) of this subsection.
13 (c) On or before December 1 of each year, the Governor shall submit a
14 letter to the House Committee on Government Operations and Military Affairs
15 and the Senate Committee on Government Operations addressing the following
16 matters:
17 (1) providing details on any informal and formal discussions and
18 negotiations involving agreements pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C.
19 § 1401(i); and
